      <h2>Safety Instructions</h2>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Never operate this Angle Grinder in Reverse motor rotation or at high speed.</strong>
      </div>

      <ul>
        <li>Always wear proper eye protection while using this attachment on your H.30 handpiece.</li>
        <li>Do not wear loose fitting clothing or jewelry. Tie back long hair.</li>
        <li>Keep your hands away from the moving accessory.</li>
        <li>Secure the workpiece in a vise or other type of clamp.</li>
        <li>Always use a proper dust collection system or wear a respirator to prevent inhalation of dust particles or other debris.</li>
        <li>Make sure your power tool is unplugged when changing accessories or performing maintenance.</li>
        <li>Do not apply excessive pressure against the wheel or disc. Let the tool do the work.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="note">
        For best performance, run the motor between half and three-quarter speed. Use a light touch on your foot pedal and avoid depressing it fully, or use a dial control. Even with gear reduction, running the motor at maximum speed is unsafe and will lead to heat, vibration, and premature wear.
      </div>

      <h2>Attaching the Angle Grinder Head to the H.30 Handpiece</h2>

      <div class="warning">
        Remove the handpiece from the flexible shaft before mounting the angle grinder.
      </div>

      <ol>
        <li>Use the chuck key to open the 3-jaw chuck on your handpiece.</li>
        <li>Insert and tighten the drive cup (A-69210) until the drive cup head is flush with the chuck jaws.</li>
        <li>Loosen the angle grinder collar holdfast screw (UA690).</li>
        <li>Align and match the square hole in the drive cup with the square inner drive shaft in the angle grinder spindle. Insert the handpiece until it bottoms out into the mounting collar.</li>
        <li>Tighten the collar holdfast screw.</li>
        <li>Check that the handpiece is engaged by turning the mounted flap wheel or accessory by hand while looking into the bottom of the handpiece to ensure that the handpiece keyway or spindle is rotating.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/foredom-angle-grinder/p02_11.jpg" alt="Assembly steps showing drive cup insertion and collar alignment" />
        <figcaption>Assembly steps 1&ndash;6: attaching the angle grinder head to the H.30 handpiece</figcaption>
      </div>

      <div class="note">
        When you are sure that the Angle Grinder head is attached properly, you can reconnect the H.30 handpiece to the flexible shaft.
      </div>

      <h2>Removing and Installing Accessories</h2>

      <h3>3/8&Prime; Diameter Arbor Hole Accessories</h3>

      <div class="warning">
        Make sure your power tool is unplugged when changing accessories.
      </div>

      <ol start="7">
        <li>To remove the flap wheel, insert the open-end wrench (A-69218) onto the flats on the angle grinder spindle through the slot in the open end of the safety shield. You may need to turn the spindle to align the flats so the wrench fits securely all the way in.</li>
        <li>While holding the open-end wrench firmly, insert the 3mm hex wrench (A-69219) into the wheel mounting screw and turn counterclockwise.</li>
        <li>Remove the 5mm Short Hub (A-69212) with 8mm screw (UA690) from the flap wheel and insert a new accessory with the same arbor hole thickness.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Selecting the Correct Hub</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Short Hub (A-69212, 5mm) with 8mm screw:</strong> For accessories with arbor hole thickness from 1/32&Prime; (1mm) to 5/32&Prime; (4mm).</li>
        <li><strong>Long Hub (A-69212L, 8mm) with 14mm screw:</strong> For accessories with arbor hole thickness from 5/32&Prime; (4mm) to 9/32&Prime; (7mm).</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="note">
        To prevent excessive run-out, always ensure that the hub extends at least 1/32&Prime; (1mm) from the bottom of the accessory into the Inner Wheel Arbor (A-69213).
      </div>

      <ol start="10">
        <li>Insert the new accessory with hub into the Inner Wheel Arbor (A-69213).</li>
        <li>Tighten the wheel mounting screw with the 3mm hex wrench while holding the open-end wrench to prevent the spindle from turning.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Installing Disc Mandrels to the Threaded Spindle</h3>

      <p>Follow steps 7&ndash;9 to remove the existing accessory and hub, then:</p>

      <ol start="12">
        <li>Remove the Inner Wheel Arbor (A-69213) by holding the open-end wrench (A-69218) in the spindle flats to prevent rotation, inserting the pins of the Face Spanner Wrench (A-69217) into the holes on the inner wheel arbor, and turning counterclockwise to unscrew and remove.</li>
        <li>Mount and screw on the mandrel (M8 &times; 1.0mm thread) such as the Disc Mandrel (A-69222), Screw-Lok Disc Mandrel (A-69225), optional Quick Change Arbor (A-69223), or optional Collet Adapter (A-69224). Hold the open-end wrench in the spindle flats to prevent rotation and tighten the mandrel snugly.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Discs must be centered.</strong> If sanding discs are installed off center it can cause vibration, premature wear of both sanding disc and mandrel, and the disc may hit the safety shield when rotating.
      </div>

      <h3>PSA Sanding Discs</h3>

      <p>The Angle Grinder comes with 9 sanding discs, a Disc Holder Protector Pad, and 5 PSA (Pressure Sensitive Adhesive) Velcro discs. To use the sanding discs with the A-69222 Disc Mandrel, a PSA Velcro disc (A-10041) must be attached to the back of the PSA sanding discs. The Velcro disc insulates the sanding disc, prevents slippage, and allows removal and reuse.</p>

      <p>To properly install sanding discs: carefully line up the sanding disc and the PSA disc with the disc mandrel so that the mandrel is centered. An even, exposed edge should be visible around the mandrel&rsquo;s edge. If it looks off center, remove and replace it until it looks centered, then press down to secure.</p>

      <h3>Screw-Lok Discs</h3>

      <p>The Screw-Lok Disc Mandrel (A-69225) screws onto the Angle Grinder and has a threaded hole for attaching discs with a plastic screw back. The sandpaper discs overhang the backing for smooth sanding edges and flexibility on sanding contours. See steps 7&ndash;13 for installation.</p>

      <h3>Quick Change Sanding Discs</h3>

      <ol start="14">
        <li>Install the Quick Change Arbor (A-69223) per steps 12&ndash;13. When the arbor is in place, select a Quick Change Disc.</li>
        <li>Align and attach the Quick Change Arbor cross bar into the cross bar mounting slot in the quick change disc back.</li>
        <li>Rotate or turn the Quick Change Disc until the cross bar is fully engaged.</li>
      </ol>

      <p>To remove Quick Change Discs, reverse steps 15&ndash;16.</p>

      <h3>Installing 2&Prime; Radial Bristle Discs</h3>

      <ol>
        <li>You can mount up to 2 Radial Bristle Discs on the 5mm Short Hub (A-69212) and up to 4 on the 8mm Long Hub (A-69212L).</li>
        <li>Mount the discs so that the bristles curve clockwise from the base to the tip (following the direction of forward motor rotation).</li>
        <li>Remove the Short Hub from the flap wheel and mount the radial bristle discs. Always ensure that the hub extends at least 1/32&Prime; (1mm) from the bottom of the accessory into the Inner Wheel Arbor (A-69213) to prevent excessive run-out.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Maintenance</h2>

      <ul>
        <li>Virtually maintenance-free; requires no lubrication.</li>
        <li><strong>Never immerse the unit in any cleaning solution.</strong></li>
        <li>Inspect the Angle Grinder and Drive Cup after every 50 hours of use.</li>
        <li>Make sure that the spindle rotates freely when removed from the H.30 handpiece.</li>
        <li>Wipe off with a damp rag only.</li>
        <li>Do not use compressed air, as dust particles may be forced into the ball bearings or gears and cause damage.</li>
      </ul>

